ric space. Let `K : ι → Set X` be a locally finite family of closed sets, let\n`U : ι → Set X` be a family of open sets such that `K i ⊆ U i` for all `i`. Then there exists a\npositive continuous function `δ : C(X, ℝ)` such that for any `i` and `x ∈ K i`, we have\n`Metric.closedBall x (δ x) ⊆ U i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/PartitionOfUnity.html#Metric.exists_continuous_real_forall_closedBall_subset","kind":"theorem","line":165,"name":"Metric.exists_continuous_real_forall_closedBall_subset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/PartitionOfUnity.lean#L165-L173"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/PartitionOfUnity.html#Metric.exists_continuous_nnreal_forall_closedBall_subset\"><span class=\"name\">Metric</span>.<span class=\"name\">exists_continuous_nnreal_forall_closedBall_subset</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">X</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/Defs.html#MetricSpace\">MetricSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K </span><span class=\"fn\">U</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ι</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span></span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span cla