sic.html#IsOpen\">IsOpen</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hKU</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hfin</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/LocallyFinite.html#LocallyFinite\">LocallyFinite</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">X</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᶠ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENNReal/Basic.html#ENNReal\">ENNReal</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <span class=\"fn\">X</span>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">in</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/SProd.html#SProd.sprod\">×ˢ</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.2</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">K</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/EMetricSpace/Defs.html#Metric.closedEBall\">closedEBall</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.2</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.1</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#HasSubset.Subset\">⊆</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">U</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `K : ι → Set X` be a locally finite family of closed sets in an emetric space. Let\n`U : ι → Set X` be a family of open sets such that `K i ⊆ U i` for all `i`. Then for any point\n`x : X`, for sufficiently small `r : ℝ≥0∞` and for `y` sufficiently close to `x`, for all `i`, if\n`y ∈ K i`, then `Metric.closedEBall y r ⊆ U i`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/PartitionOfUnity.html#Metric.eventually_nhds_zero_forall_closedEBall_subset","kind":"theorem","line":40,"name":"Metric.eventually_nhds_zero_forall_closedEBall_subset","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/PartitionOfUnity.lean#L40-L63"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.EMetricSpace.Paracompact","Mathlib.Topology.Instances.ENNReal.Lemmas","Mathlib.Analysis.Convex.PartitionOfUnity"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.PartitionOfUnity"}